63%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Teen's%20AI%20Company%20Launched%20In%202022%20Now%20Valued%20At%20Rs%20100%20Crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPranjali%20Awasthi%2C%20a%2016-year-old%20Indian%20prodigy%20has%20made%20it%20into%20the%20technology%20world%20with%20her%20venture%2C%20Delv.AI%2C%20a%20startup%20dedicated%20to%20refining%20the%20process%20of%20data%20extraction%20for%20research.%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fpranjali-awasthi-neuro%2F%5C%22%3EMs%20Awasthi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20launched%20the%20company%20in%20January%202022%20and%20has%20already%20raised%20%24450%2C000%20(Rs%203.7%20crore)%20in%20funding.%20Ms%20Awasthi%20has%20a%20team%20of%20up%20to%2010%20employees.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20journey%20with%20technology%20started%20young%2C%20and%20she%20has%20credited%20her%20father%2C%20an%20engineer%20as%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20inspiration%20for%20her%20entrepreneurial%20journey.%20She%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.in%2Ftech%2Fnews%2Fim-a-16-year-old-ai-founder-people-look-down-on-me-literally-and-figuratively-but-ive-already-raised-450000-%2Farticleshow%2F104283183.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20her%20father's%20passion%20and%20values%20encouraged%20her%20to%20get%20into%20coding%20when%20she%20was%207.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20the%20media%20outlet%20that%20she%20moved%20to%20Florida%20with%20family%20at%20age%2011%20from%20India%20and%20the%20world%20of%20computer%20science%20and%20competitive%20math%20opened%20up%20for%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20age%20of%2013%2C%20she%20started%20interning%20in%20university%20research%20labs%20at%20Florida%20Internal%20University%20working%20on%20machine%20learning%20projects%20alongside%20going%20to%20school.%20During%20COVID%2C%20she%20used%20to%20intern%20for%20about%2020%20hours%20a%20week%20because%20her%20school%20had%20gone%20virtual.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20her%20internship%20days%2C%20she%20started%20thinking%20about%20how%20AI%20could%20solve%20the%20problem%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20Delv.AI%20came%20about.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20Pranjali%20won%20a%20place%20at%20an%20AI%20startup%20accelerator%20in%20Miami%2C%20facilitated%20by%20tech%20enthusiasts%20Lucy%20Guo%20and%20Dave%20Fontenot%20from%20Backend%20Capital.%20She%20was%20accepted%20into%20their%20September%2012-week%20cohort%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20small%20piece%20of%20her%20future%20company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20momentarily%20stepped%20away%20from%20high%20school.%20The%20accelerator%20became%20the%20launchpad%20and%20helped%20her%20in%20attracting%20investments%20from%20prominent%20names%20including%20On%20Deck%20and%20Village%20Global.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20that%20Delv.AI's%20primary%20objective%20is%20to%20aid%20researchers%20in%20accessing%20specific%20information%20within%20the%20realm%20of%20online%20content.%20Delv.AI%20raised%20%24450%2C000%20(approximately%20Rs%203.7%20crore)%20in%20funding%20and%20currently%20boasts%20an%20approximate%20valuation%20of%20%2412%20million%20(Rs%20100%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697016480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Ffp95brv_pranjali-awasthi_625x300_11_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2F16-year-old-indian-girls-ai-company-launched-in-2022-now-valued-at-rs-100-crore-4470684%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pranjali%20Awasthi's%20Delv.AI%20raised%20Rs%203.7%20crore%20in%20funding%20and%20currently%20boasts%20an%20approximate%20valuation%20of%20Rs%20100%20crore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2F16-year-old-indian-girls-ai-company-launched-in-2022-now-valued-at-rs-100-crore-4470684%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%