ime%20and%20again%20forced%20him%20to%20use%20all%20legal%20and%20illegal%20means%2C%20including%20the%20use%20of%20torture%20and%20anti-terrorism%20laws%2C%20to%20force%20businessman%20Mian%20Nasir%20Janjua%20to%20give%20a%20false%20confessional%20statement%20against%20PML-N%20Senior%20Vice%20President%20Maryam%20Nawaz%20in%20the%20judge%20Arshed%20Malik%20video%20scandal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Memon%20said%20it%20was%20planned%20in%20the%20PM%20House%20that%20Mr%20Janjua%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%2030-years-old%20trusted%20friend%20of%20Sharif%2C%20should%20be%20made%20the%20main%20culprit%20since%20he%20is%20a%20businessman%20and%20would%20be%20an%20easy%20target%20to%20become%20an%20approver%20against%20Maryam%20and%20senior%20PML-N%20leadership.%20Mr%20Janjua%20then%20left%20Pakistan%20for%20London%20and%20didn't%20return%20until%20Imran%20Khan%20was%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20PML-N%20Senators%20Ishaq%20Dar%20and%20Irfan%20Siddiqui%20said%20Sharif%20would%20leave%20for%20Saudi%20Arabia%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERefuting%20rumours%20pertaining%20to%20Sharif's%20presence%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Irfan%20Siddiqui%20confirmed%20that%20the%20former%20prime%20minister%20is%20still%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20and%20that%20the%20visit%20to%20Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20of%20a%20private%20nature%20as%20the%20ex-premier%20will%20perform%20Umrah.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIshaq%20Dar%20said%20that%20there%20is%20no%20chance%20of%20Sharif%20being%20arrested%20on%20return%20to%20Pakistan.%20He%20said%20that%20transit%20bail%20and%20protective%20bail%20would%20be%20obtained%20from%20the%20court.%20%26quot%3BNawaz%20will%20follow%20the%20standard%20legal%20procedures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20PML-N's%20narrative%20would%20be%20around%20the%20economy.%20Dar%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BRecovery%20of%20the%20economy%20is%20the%20best%20revenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENawaz%20Sharif%20stepped%20down%20as%20the%20country's%20Pri